I don't see this as a bad thing.  In fact, here is why I think verants policy on the rate of entry is misguided.<br>
<br>
High end content is designed with the click stick in mind.  A guild just can't function well and efficiently without several clicky clerics at a raid for a whipe out.  If your click clerics don't show up, your 5 minuet CR just turned into a 45 minuet process.<br>
<br>
The high end games seems designed around the assumption that you will have click sticks present.  Therefore saying that not all clerics should have a click stick goes against the design of encounters.<br>
<br>
Their policy does not match their design, in my opinion. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=200411">Batou of The Nexus</a><BR>
